div.p:
Sometimes he had a mind to hear himſelf reviled;
                     Bonavent. p. 39. Legenda Antonin. p. 725. Legenda.
                   and to this purpoſe he once ſaid to a Monk, Rail on me. Which ſtrict command the Monk not daring to diſobey, ſaid to him, Thou art an idle, lazie Lubber, a mercenary fellow, an ignorant ſott, and a worthleſs raſcal. Whereat St. Francis greatly rejoycing, anſwered, God bleſs thee, my Son;

 for what thou haſt ſaid is vory true.
